**High Findings**

1. `brief-gatekeeper` is not independent. It actively routes to an external `/role-architect` workflow, including “Role Architect 호출” in the main flow and an explicit `/role-architect` command in the procedure. That violates the approved independence constraint that adopted skills complete from their own `SKILL.md` and references only. Sources: `.claude/skills/brief-gatekeeper/SKILL.md:50`, `.claude/skills/brief-gatekeeper/SKILL.md:131`, `.claude/skills/brief-gatekeeper/SKILL.md:146`, `.claude/skills/brief-gatekeeper/references/procedure.md:211`, `.claude/skills/brief-gatekeeper/references/procedure.md:214`, plan lines `/Users/tw.kim/.claude/plans/documents-aga-test-openclaw-cloud-claud-merry-harp.md:11`.

2. `code-quality` has dangling/cross-skill references, so it is not self-contained. `failure-messages.md` links to `../../planner/references/clean-architecture.md` and names `.claude/skills/planner/references/clean-architecture.md`; those files are absent in this repo. It also points users to `.claude/skills/best-practices/` and `/solve`, which violates the “no route/ref to other skills” adoption constraint. Sources: `.claude/skills/code-quality/references/failure-messages.md:300`, `.claude/skills/code-quality/references/failure-messages.md:346`, `.claude/skills/code-quality/references/failure-messages.md:347`, `.claude/skills/code-quality/references/failure-messages.md:348`.

3. `best-practices` is not fully curated to the Expo RN repo stack. The adopted rules still include source-project/web-specific material: `test-infrastructure` references `admin-api`, `billing-api`, `admin-portal`, `npm`, and `npx`; `ts-validation-zod-schema` keeps a “Next.js API route example”; React rules include browser DOM/window and HTML anchor/div examples. This conflicts with the request to keep RN-applicable React, backend/contracts, and test infrastructure curated for this repo. Sources: `.claude/skills/best-practices/rules/test-infrastructure.md:3`, `.claude/skills/best-practices/rules/test-infrastructure.md:7`, `.claude/skills/best-practices/rules/test-infrastructure.md:13`, `.claude/skills/best-practices/rules/ts-validation-zod-schema.md:70`, `.claude/skills/best-practices/rules/react-rerender-transitions.md:21`, `.claude/skills/best-practices/rules/react-components-composition.md:26`.

**Medium Findings**

4. The requested changes are ignored by Git, so PR readiness is not proven. `.gitignore` ignores both `CLAUDE.md` and `.claude/`, and `git status --short --ignored -- .claude CLAUDE.md .codex .agents` reports `!! .claude/` and `!! CLAUDE.md`. This means the reviewed additions are local ignored files unless the implementation explicitly unignores or force-adds them. Sources: `.gitignore:7`, `.gitignore:8`, AGENTS PR expectation `AGENTS.md:104`.

5. No implementation evidence file with validation command results was provided for this adoption. The only scoped evidence under `.evidence/wm/claude-skill-adoption/` is the review prompt, while repo DoD expects applicable verification before PR. Sources: `.evidence/wm/claude-skill-adoption/20260613-adoption-review-prompt.md:1`, `AGENTS.md:106`, `AGENTS.md:107`.

**Low Findings**

6. `code-quality` still contains Python examples despite the declared stack context being Expo RN + TypeScript + `packages/contracts`. This is less severe than the dangling references, but it is another curation mismatch. Source: `.claude/skills/code-quality/references/failure-messages.md:122`.

